    %h2 Adding Icons to Buttons
    %p The jQuery Mobile framework includes a selected set of icons most often needed for mobile apps. To minimize download size, jQuery Mobile includes a single white icon sprite, and automatically adds a semi-transparent black circle behind the icon to ensure that it has good contrast on any background color.
    %p
      An icon can be added to a button by adding a
      %code data-icon
      attribute on the anchor specifying the icon to display.  For example, the following markup:
    %code
      &lt;a href=&quot;index.html&quot; data-role=&quot;button&quot;
      data-icon=&quot;delete&quot;
      &gt;Delete&lt;/a&gt;
    %p Creates this button with an icon:
    %a{"data-icon" => "delete", "data-role" => "button", :href => "/mobile/docs/buttons"} Delete
