    %h2 Icon positioning
    %p By default, all icons in buttons are placed to the left of the button text.
    %a{"data-icon" => "delete", "data-iconpos" => "left", "data-role" => "button", :href => "/mobile/docs/buttons"} Delete
    %p
      This default may be overridden using the
      %code data-iconpos
      attribute to set the icon to the right, above (top) or below (bottom) the text. For example, the markup:
    %code
      &lt;a href=&quot;index.html&quot; data-role=&quot;button&quot; data-icon=&quot;delete&quot;
      data-iconpos=&quot;right&quot;
      &gt;Delete&lt;/a&gt;
    %p Creates this button with right-aligned icon:
    %a{"data-icon" => "delete", "data-iconpos" => "right", "data-role" => "button", :href => "/mobile/docs/buttons"} Delete
    %p
      Icons can also be positioned above the text by specifying
      %code data-iconpos="top"
    %a{"data-icon" => "delete", "data-iconpos" => "top", "data-role" => "button", :href => "/mobile/docs/buttons"} Delete
    %p
      Or icons can also be positioned below the text by specifying
      %code data-iconpos="bottom"
    %a{"data-icon" => "delete", "data-iconpos" => "bottom", "data-role" => "button", :href => "/mobile/docs/buttons"} Delete
    %p
      You can also create an icon-only button, by setting the
      %code data-iconpos
      attribute to
      = succeed "." do
        %code notext
      The button plugin will hide the text on-screen, but add it as a
      %code title
      attribute on the link to provide context for screen readers and devices that support tooltips. For example, replacing
      %code data-iconpos="right"
      on the previous example with
      = succeed ":" do
        %code data-iconpos="notext"
    %code
      &lt;a href=&quot;index.html&quot; data-role=&quot;button&quot; data-icon=&quot;delete&quot;
      data-iconpos=&quot;right&quot;
      &gt;Delete&lt;/a&gt;
      
    %p Creates this icon-only button:
    %a{"data-icon" => "delete", "data-iconpos" => "notext", "data-role" => "button", :href => "/mobile/docs/buttons"} Delete
    %h2 Custom Icons
    %p
      To use custom icons, specify a
      %code data-icon
      value that has a unique name like
      %code myapp-email
      and the button plugin will generate a class by prefixing
      %code ui-icon-
      to the
      %code data-icon
      value and apply it to the button. You can then write a CSS rule that targets the
      %code ui-icon-myapp-email
      class to specify the icon background source. To maintain visual consistency, create a white icon 18x18 pixels saved as a PNG-8 with alpha transparency.
